  "reasoning": "## Forecast Summary: Brent Crude Oil on March 12, 2026\n\n**Central estimate: ~$85/bbl** with wide uncertainty due to the ongoing Iran-US war.\n\n### Key Context\n- The US-Israel military operation against Iran began Feb 28, killing Supreme Leader Khamenei\n- Iran closed the Strait of Hormuz in retaliation, cutting ~20% of global oil supply\n- Brent spiked from ~$72 to $84+ in 2 trading days\n- Active combat continues with no ceasefire talks\n\n### Distribution (Percentiles)\n\n| Percentile | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| P10 | $72.00 |\n| P20 | $76.50 |\n| P40 | $82.50 |\n| P60 | $87.00 |\n| P80 | $93.00 |\n| P90 | $97.00 |\n\n### Scenario Weights\n- **War continues / Hormuz closed (65%)**: Mode ~$86, range $76-97\n- **Escalation (15%)**: Mode ~$92, range $80-108\n- **De-escalation begins (15%)**: Mode ~$75, range $66-86\n- **Quick resolution (5%)**: Mode ~$68, range $60-78\n\nThe distribution is right-skewed — the risk of escalation (Iran attacking Saudi/UAE oil infrastructure, broader regional war) carries more upside potential than the limited probability of rapid de-escalation within 7 trading days.",
